    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-12-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-12-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="60"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d60">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Storer</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-12-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 15, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 123.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    dispatch No. 186, of the 29th ultimo, concerning the complaint of Mrs. Maria
                    Horniak in regard to the seizure of her prepaid ticket and her treatment by
                    Hungarian <pb facs="0180" n="92" xml:id="pg_92"/> officials and reporting your
                    interview with the under secretary of state on the subject of Hungarian
                    emigration.</p>
                <p>The Department is pleased to note the disposition of the Austro-Hungarian foreign
                    office to promptly investigate the complaints made by American citizens and to
                    see that justice is done in each case.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
